Here's a diagram of the algebraic setup. All the arrows are inclusions.
$$
\require{AMScd}
\begin{CD}
A @>>> A \otimes_B L @>>> K\\
@AAA @AAA\\
B @>>>L
\end{CD}
$$
Since $K$ is finite over $L$ you know that algebra generators for $A$ over $B$ satisfy monic polynomials with coefficients in $L$. If you localize $B$ at a well-chosen element $f$ you can upgrade this statement!
